content.description: Climb directly up and pull roof. Awesome holds and great movement. Some loose rock in the middle of this one.
content.protection: 2 bolt anchor can be accessed from above probably. Otherwise climb radical cleft to set up rope.
content.location: Start just right of Radical cLeft on right trending black sloping holds.

content.description: Favorite line on the wall. Movement to the ledge is delicate and thoughtful. Fun big holds till the finish.
content.location: Start below and right of roof.

content.description: Fun 5.8 crack rail with a 10a sequence to your first piece of gear.
content.protection: single rack 0.2 - 3. 2 bolt anchor on mossy ledge above roof.
content.location: Start below furthest left part of roof. Climb up then right till roof ends and pull through fun jugs at the end to a mossy topout.

content.description: Beautiful golden granite with great edges & crimps unique to the other walls around. A ledge in the middle of the wall keeps all of the current + prospective routes in the moderate range of grades.
